## Goals

The purpose of this tutorial is to demonstrate how content creators can easily add assets to games with Unreal Engine 4 (UE4). By the end of this quick start guide, content creators will know how to use the **Project Browser** to create new projects; navigate the **Content Browser** to find and add content; know where to find information on the **FBX Content Pipeline**; and use the **Material Editor** to modify **Materials** before applying them to a **Static Mesh Actor**.

## Objectives

By the end of this quick start guide, you'll be able to:

* Set-up a Project
* Create Materials
* Edit Materials
* Apply Materials to a Static Mesh Actor

